      <% } %>
      <a class="help-nav-item" href="#" onclick="showHelpSection('files')">Files & Attachments</a>

      <% if (user.role_name === 'CLIENT_ADMIN') { %>
        <div class="help-nav-section">Administration</div>
        <a class="help-nav-item" href="#" onclick="showHelpSection('roles')">Roles & Hierarchy</a>
        <a class="help-nav-item" href="#" onclick="showHelpSection('team-mgmt')">Team Management</a>
        <a class="help-nav-item" href="#" onclick="showHelpSection('permissions')">Permissions Matrix</a>
      <% } %>

      <div class="help-nav-section">Account & Security</div>
      <a class="help-nav-item" href="#" onclick="showHelpSection('security')">Security & Sessions</a>
      <a class="help-nav-item" href="#" onclick="showHelpSection('settings')">Settings & Password</a>

      <div class="help-nav-section">Support</div>
      <a class="help-nav-item" href="#" onclick="showHelpSection('tips')">Tips & Shortcuts</a>
      <a class="help-nav-item" href="#" onclick="showHelpSection('troubleshooting')">Troubleshooting</a>
      <a class="help-nav-item" href="#" onclick="showHelpSection('faq')">FAQ</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="help-content" id="helpContent">

    <!-- ═══ OVERVIEW ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-overview">
      <h4>Welcome to the Client Portal</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">Your private communication and task management hub. Everything you need to collaborate with your team and monitor work — all in one place.</p>

      <div class="help-cards">
        <div class="help-card">
          <div class="help-card-icon"><i class="bi bi-chat-dots-fill"></i></div>
          <h6>Chat</h6>
          <p>Private 1-to-1 and group conversations with your team. Share files, images, and stay connected in real-time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="help-card">
          <div class="help-card-icon"><i class="bi bi-kanban-fill"></i></div>
          <h6>Tasks</h6>
          <p>Create, assign, and track tasks with priority levels, due dates, and threaded correspondence.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="help-card">
          <div class="help-card-icon"><i class="bi bi-journal-text"></i></div>
          <h6>Notes</h6>
          <p>Personal notepad with auto-save, search, pin, export, and voice dictation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="help-card">
          <div class="help-card-icon"><i class="bi bi-flag-fill"></i></div>
          <h6>Team India</h6>
          <p>Live employee status dashboard. See who's working, what they're doing, and chat with them directly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="help-card">
          <div class="help-card-icon"><i class="bi bi-headset"></i></div>
          <h6>Admin Chat</h6>
          <p>Direct line to the local admin. Always one click away from any page in the portal.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="help-card">
          <div class="help-card-icon"><i class="bi bi-shield-lock-fill"></i></div>
          <h6>Private & Secure</h6>
          <p>The entire portal is invisible to the local team. Your conversations, tasks, and notes are completely private.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FIRST LOGIN ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-first-login" style="display:none">
      <h4>First Login Guide</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">New to the portal? Here's everything you need to get started in 5 minutes.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Step 1: Log In</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Open the portal URL in your browser (Chrome or Edge recommended)</li>
          <li>Enter the <strong>email</strong> and <strong>password</strong> provided by your admin</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Login</strong> — you'll land on the CFC Portal home page with quick links to all sections</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          If you can't log in, contact your admin to verify your credentials or check if your account is active.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Step 2: Change Your Password</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Click your <strong>avatar</strong> at the bottom of the left sidebar</li>
          <li>Select <strong>Change Password</strong></li>
          <li>Set a new password (minimum 6 characters) and confirm it</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="help-callout warning">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill me-2"></i>
          We strongly recommend changing your default password immediately after your first login.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Step 3: Choose Your Theme</h6>
        <p>Click the <strong>sun/moon icon</strong> in the left sidebar to switch between dark and light mode. Your preference is saved automatically.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Step 4: Explore the Portal</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-chat-dots me-2"></i><strong>Chat</strong></td><td>Start a conversation with a team member</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-kanban me-2"></i><strong>Tasks</strong></td><td>View tasks assigned to you, or create a new one</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-journal-text me-2"></i><strong>Notes</strong></td><td>Create a personal note — it auto-saves as you type</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-headset me-2"></i><strong>Support</strong></td><td>Click the headset icon in the sidebar to chat with local admin</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Step 5: Know Your Notifications</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>You'll hear a <strong>notification sound</strong> when you receive a new message or task</li>
          <li><strong>Toast messages</strong> appear in the top-right — click them to navigate directly</li>
          <li>Unread message badges show on the Chat tab and sidebar</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ NAVIGATION ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-navigation" style="display:none">
      <h4>Navigation Guide</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">The portal uses a left sidebar for navigation with an optional home launcher page.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-house me-2"></i>Home Page</h6>
        <p>When you first log in, you'll see the <strong>CFC Portal Home</strong> page with large icon tiles for every section. Click any tile to jump directly to that feature. You can return to the home page at any time by clicking the <strong>"C" logo</strong> at the top of the sidebar.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-layout-sidebar me-2"></i>Sidebar (Activity Bar)</h6>
        <p>The left sidebar provides quick access to all portal sections. It has two modes:</p>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Collapsed</strong></td><td>Thin icon-only bar (default). Hover over any icon to see its label as a tooltip.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Expanded</strong></td><td>Wider bar showing icons with text labels. Click the <strong>chevron button (<i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i>)</strong> below the logo to toggle between modes. Your preference is remembered across sessions.</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-list me-2"></i>Sidebar Sections</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-chat-dots-fill me-2"></i><strong>Chat</strong></td><td>All your conversations — 1-to-1 and group chats</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-kanban-fill me-2"></i><strong>Tasks</strong></td><td>Task board — create, assign, track, and comment on tasks</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-journal-text me-2"></i><strong>Notes</strong></td><td>Your personal notes with auto-save and dictation</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-flag-fill me-2"></i><strong>Team India</strong></td><td>Live employee status and bridge chat (Admin & Top Mgmt only)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-people-fill me-2"></i><strong>Users</strong></td><td>Manage portal users — add, edit, deactivate (Admin only)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-question-circle me-2"></i><strong>Help</strong></td><td>This help & training section</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-gear me-2"></i>Bottom Sidebar Actions</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-headset me-2"></i><strong>Support</strong></td><td>Opens a direct chat with the local admin from any page</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-sun me-2"></i><strong>Theme</strong></td><td>Switch between dark and light mode (preference saved automatically)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-person-circle me-2"></i><strong>Profile Menu</strong></td><td>Change password, view your email, logout</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-bell me-2"></i>Notification Indicators</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Chat badge</strong></td><td>Red number on Chat icon showing total unread messages</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Sidebar badge</strong></td><td>Individual unread count next to each conversation</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Toast popups</strong></td><td>Slide-in alerts in top-right for new messages, tasks, and status changes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Sound alert</strong></td><td>Notification tone plays for new messages and task events</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ CHAT ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-chat" style="display:none">
      <h4>Chat</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">Real-time messaging with your team — private and secure.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Starting a Chat</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Click <strong>+ New Chat</strong> or the contact list to start a 1-to-1 conversation</li>
          <li>Click <strong>New Group</strong> to create a group chat (give it a name and select members)</li>
          <li>Every conversation is private — only participants can see it</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          <strong>Who can create groups?</strong> Admin, Top Management, Management, and Managers can create group chats. Users can only participate in groups they're added to.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Messaging Features</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-send me-2"></i><strong>Send Message</strong></td><td>Type and press Enter (or click send). Shift+Enter for new line.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-paperclip me-2"></i><strong>Send Files</strong></td><td>Click paperclip to attach images, documents, or any file (max 100 MB per file)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-emoji-smile me-2"></i><strong>Emojis</strong></td><td>Click smiley face to insert emojis. Click anywhere outside to close the picker.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-mic me-2"></i><strong>Dictation</strong></td><td>Click microphone to speak your message (Chrome/Edge). Click again to stop.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-search me-2"></i><strong>Search</strong></td><td>Click search icon in chat header to find messages within the conversation</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Editing & Deleting Messages</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-pencil me-2"></i><strong>Edit Message</strong></td><td>Hover over your sent message, click the three-dot menu, select <strong>Edit</strong>. The message will show <em>(edited)</em> after saving.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-trash me-2"></i><strong>Delete Message</strong></td><td>Hover over your sent message, click the three-dot menu, select <strong>Delete</strong>. The message will show <em>"This message was deleted"</em> for everyone.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-file-earmark-x me-2"></i><strong>Delete File</strong></td><td>You can delete file/image messages the same way. The file is permanently removed from the server.</td></tr>
        </table>
        <div class="help-callout warning">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill me-2"></i>
          You can only edit or delete your own messages. Deleted messages and files cannot be recovered.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Message Status Indicators</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-check"></i> Single tick</td><td>Message sent to the server</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-check-all"></i> Double tick (grey)</td><td>Message delivered</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-check-all" style="color:#34b7f1"></i> Double tick (blue)</td><td>Message read by recipient</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="online-dot-sm" style="display:inline-block"></span> Green dot</td><td>User is currently online in the portal</td></tr>
          <tr><td><em>typing...</em></td><td>The other person is typing a message</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Group Chat Management</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Click the <strong>people icon</strong> in chat header to see group members</li>
          <li>Add new members from the modal — select from your team list</li>
          <li>Remove a member by clicking the <strong>X</strong> next to their name</li>
          <li>Only the group creator or authorized roles can manage members</li>
          <li>When you add someone, they can see all messages from that point forward</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Date Separators & Scroll Loading</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Messages are grouped by date with labels like <strong>Today</strong>, <strong>Yesterday</strong>, or the full date</li>
          <li>Scroll up to automatically load older messages — no need to click anything</li>
          <li>URLs pasted in messages automatically become clickable links</li>
          <li>Image files show an inline preview thumbnail — click to view full size</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ TASKS ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-tasks" style="display:none">
      <h4>Tasks</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">Create, assign, and track work with full correspondence.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Creating a Task</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Click <strong>New Task</strong> button</li>
          <li>Fill in: Title (required), Description, Priority, Due Date, Assignee</li>
          <li>Use the <strong>mic button</strong> to dictate title or description</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Create Task</strong></li>
        </ol>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          <strong>Who can you assign to?</strong> You can assign tasks to people at your level or below in the hierarchy — never upward. Users cannot create tasks.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Priority Levels</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><span class="priority-badge priority-urgent">URGENT</span></td><td>Immediate attention required — shows prominently in red</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="priority-badge priority-high">HIGH</span></td><td>Important, should be done today</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="priority-badge priority-medium">MEDIUM</span></td><td>Standard priority — default for most tasks</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="priority-badge priority-low">LOW</span></td><td>Can wait, no rush</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Task Status Flow</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><span class="status-badge status-open">OPEN</span></td><td>Newly created, not started yet</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="status-badge status-in_progress">IN PROGRESS</span></td><td>Being actively worked on</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="status-badge status-completed"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill me-1"></i>DONE</span></td><td>Completed — creator gets a success notification</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="status-badge status-cancelled">CANCELLED</span></td><td>No longer needed</td></tr>
        </table>
        <div class="help-callout success">
          <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          When a task is marked <strong>Done</strong>, the task creator receives a toast notification with a celebration message and sound.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Task Correspondence (Comments)</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Click any task to open its detail panel on the right</li>
          <li>Add comments in the correspondence area at the bottom</li>
          <li>Attach files to comments using the <strong>paperclip</strong> button (max 100 MB)</li>
          <li>Use the <strong>mic</strong> button to dictate comments</li>
          <li>Use <strong>emojis</strong> in your comments</li>
          <li><strong>Edit</strong> your own comments by hovering and clicking the pencil icon — edited comments show <em>(edited)</em></li>
          <li>Both the task creator and assignee receive notifications for new comments</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Filtering Tasks</h6>
        <p>Use the filter bar at the top to narrow down your task list:</p>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Status filter</strong></td><td>Show only Open, In Progress, Done, or Cancelled tasks</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Priority filter</strong></td><td>Show only Urgent, High, Medium, or Low tasks</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Search</strong></td><td>Type to search tasks by title</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Overdue Tasks</h6>
        <p>Tasks past their due date show a red <strong>OVERDUE</strong> badge and a red left border. To resolve, either:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Update the task status to <strong>Done</strong> or <strong>Cancelled</strong></li>
          <li>Extend the due date to a future date</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Task Notifications</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-bell me-2"></i><strong>New task assigned</strong></td><td>Toast notification with sound to the assignee</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-arrow-repeat me-2"></i><strong>Status changed</strong></td><td>Toast to both creator and assignee</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-chat-left-text me-2"></i><strong>New comment</strong></td><td>Toast to creator and assignee</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-clock me-2"></i><strong>Due today</strong></td><td>Reminder toast on page load</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-check-circle me-2"></i><strong>Task completed</strong></td><td>Success toast with celebration to creator</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ NOTES ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-notes" style="display:none">
      <h4>Notes & Dictation</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">Your personal notepad — auto-saves as you type. Only you can see your notes.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Using Notes</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-plus-lg me-2"></i><strong>Create</strong></td><td>Click the + button. A new note opens with a date/time stamp as the title.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-pencil me-2"></i><strong>Edit</strong></td><td>Just type — auto-saves 2 seconds after you stop typing. No save button needed.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-search me-2"></i><strong>Search</strong></td><td>Type in the search bar to find notes by title or content.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-pin-angle me-2"></i><strong>Pin</strong></td><td>Click the pin icon to keep important notes at the top of the list. Click again to unpin.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-file-text me-2"></i><strong>Export as Text</strong></td><td>Click the file icon to download note as a .txt file to your computer.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-printer me-2"></i><strong>Print / PDF</strong></td><td>Click the printer icon to open a print-friendly version. Use your browser's "Save as PDF" to make a PDF.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-trash me-2"></i><strong>Delete</strong></td><td>Click the trash icon. You'll be asked to confirm before the note is permanently deleted.</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Voice Dictation</h6>
        <p>Dictation is available everywhere in the portal — notes, chat, task creation, and task comments.</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Click the <strong>microphone icon</strong> <i class="bi bi-mic"></i> next to any text input</li>
          <li>The button turns <strong style="color:var(--tf-danger)">red</strong> and pulses — you're being heard</li>
          <li>Speak naturally — text appears in the field in real-time</li>
          <li>Click the mic again (or it turns off automatically when you stop speaking)</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          <strong>Browser Support:</strong> Dictation works best in <strong>Google Chrome</strong> and <strong>Microsoft Edge</strong>. Safari has limited support. Firefox does not support it yet. If the mic icon doesn't respond, check that your browser has microphone permission enabled.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Tips for Notes</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Notes are <strong>personal</strong> — no one else can see them, not even the admin</li>
          <li>You can have unlimited notes</li>
          <li>Pinned notes always appear at the top regardless of when they were last edited</li>
          <li>The auto-save indicator appears briefly when your note is saved</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ ADMIN CHAT ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-admin-chat" style="display:none">
      <h4>Admin Chat</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">A dedicated direct line to the local admin — always one click away from any page.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>What is Admin Chat?</h6>
        <p>The Admin Chat is a special bridge chat that connects you directly with the local team's admin. Unlike portal chat (which is between portal users), this crosses the boundary and reaches the local team admin.</p>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          This is the <strong>only</strong> way to communicate with the local admin from the portal. The local admin sees your messages in a floating chat widget on their side.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>How to Use</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Click the <strong><i class="bi bi-headset"></i> Admin Chat</strong> button in the top-right corner of any page</li>
          <li>A chat panel slides open on the right side</li>
          <li>Type your message and press Enter or click Send</li>
          <li>You can also <strong>send files</strong> (paperclip icon) and use <strong>dictation</strong> (mic icon)</li>
          <li>Click the <strong>X</strong> button or click outside to close the panel</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Features</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-chat-text me-2"></i><strong>Text messages</strong></td><td>Full real-time messaging like any other chat</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-paperclip me-2"></i><strong>File sharing</strong></td><td>Send documents, images, or any file (max 100 MB)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-mic me-2"></i><strong>Dictation</strong></td><td>Speak your message using the mic button</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-trash me-2"></i><strong>Delete messages</strong></td><td>Delete your own messages — file is removed from server too</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-bell me-2"></i><strong>Notifications</strong></td><td>Toast + sound when admin replies (unless the panel is open)</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Good to Know</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Admin Chat is available from <strong>every page</strong> in the portal — chat, tasks, notes, team india, help, everywhere</li>
          <li>Your conversation persists — close the panel and reopen it, your history is still there</li>
          <li>The local admin sees all portal user conversations in a floating widget on their dashboard</li>
          <li>If the admin is offline, your message is still delivered — they'll see it when they log in</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ TEAM INDIA ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-team-india" style="display:none">
      <h4>Team India</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">Live dashboard showing your India team's work status. Available to Admin and Top Management only.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Status Table</h6>
        <p>Each row in the table represents one employee on the India team. The status badge tells you what they're doing right now:</p>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><span class="ts-badge ts-working">Working</span></td><td>Currently active on a task</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="ts-badge ts-idle">Idle</span></td><td>Logged in but no active task</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="ts-badge ts-absent">Not Logged In</span></td><td>Should be working but hasn't logged in</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="ts-badge ts-extending">Extending Shift</span></td><td>Still working after their shift ended</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="ts-badge ts-off">Off Shift</span></td><td>Not on duty right now</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="ts-badge ts-off">Week Off</span></td><td>Scheduled day off</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="ts-badge ts-leave">On Leave</span></td><td>Approved leave</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-chevron-expand me-2"></i>Task Accordion (Expand / Collapse)</h6>
        <p>Each employee row has a <strong>chevron arrow (<i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i>)</strong> on the left. Use it to quickly view all of an employee's tasks for the day without leaving the table:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Click the <strong>chevron</strong> on any row to expand it — all their day's tasks appear directly below the row</li>
          <li>Each task shows its <strong>title</strong>, <strong>status</strong> (In Progress, Pending, Done), and <strong>type</strong> (Recurring or Ad-hoc)</li>
          <li>The currently active task (if any) is highlighted with a blue accent border</li>
          <li>Click the chevron again to collapse the row back</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          Use the <strong>Expand All / Collapse All</strong> button in the header to toggle all employees at once — great for a full overview of the entire team's workload.
        </div>
        <p>When a row is collapsed, the <strong>Current Task</strong> column still shows the task the employee is currently working on, so you always have a quick glance at-a-glance view.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Employee Detail Panel</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Click any <strong>employee's name</strong> to open their detail panel on the right</li>
          <li><strong>Today's Tasks</strong> tab shows their current tasks with status and priority</li>
          <li><strong>Chat</strong> tab lets you message them directly via bridge chat</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Auto-Refresh</h6>
        <p>The table refreshes every <strong>30 seconds</strong> automatically. You'll always see the latest status without reloading the page. Expanded accordion rows stay open after a refresh.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ BRIDGE CHAT ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-bridge-chat" style="display:none">
      <h4>Bridge Chat</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">Direct messaging between portal users and local team employees — bridging the two sides.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>What is Bridge Chat?</h6>
        <p>Bridge Chat is a special chat system that crosses the boundary between the Client Portal and the local TaskFlow. It allows you to message individual employees on the India team directly.</p>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          Bridge Chat is different from regular portal chat. Portal chat is between portal users only. Bridge chat connects you to the local team employees.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>How to Start a Bridge Chat</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Go to <strong>Team India</strong> page</li>
          <li>Click on any employee row to open their panel</li>
          <li>Click the <strong>Chat</strong> tab inside the employee panel</li>
          <li>Type your message and send — the employee sees it in a floating widget on their TaskFlow dashboard</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Bridge Chat Features</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-chat-text me-2"></i><strong>Text messages</strong></td><td>Real-time messaging between portal and local team</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-paperclip me-2"></i><strong>File sharing</strong></td><td>Send documents, images, and files (max 100 MB)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-mic me-2"></i><strong>Dictation</strong></td><td>Use voice input for messages</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-trash me-2"></i><strong>Delete messages</strong></td><td>Remove your own messages and files</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-bell me-2"></i><strong>Notifications</strong></td><td>Toast + sound when the employee replies</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Important Notes</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Each conversation is between <strong>one portal user</strong> and <strong>one local employee</strong></li>
          <li>The local employee sees your messages in a floating chat widget on their side</li>
          <li>Messages are delivered even if the employee is offline — they'll see them when they log in</li>
          <li>Bridge chat files are stored separately from portal chat files for security</li>
          <li>The local team cannot initiate bridge chats — only portal users can start them</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FILES & ATTACHMENTS ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-files" style="display:none">
      <h4>Files & Attachments</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">Everything you need to know about sharing files in the portal.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>File Size Limit</h6>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          Maximum file size: <strong>100 MB</strong> per file. This applies to all file uploads — chat, task comments, admin chat, and bridge chat.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Where Can You Send Files?</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-chat-dots me-2"></i><strong>Portal Chat</strong></td><td>Click the paperclip icon in any conversation</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-kanban me-2"></i><strong>Task Comments</strong></td><td>Click the paperclip icon in the task correspondence area</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-headset me-2"></i><strong>Admin Chat</strong></td><td>Click the paperclip icon in the admin chat panel</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-flag me-2"></i><strong>Bridge Chat</strong></td><td>Click the paperclip icon in the Team India employee chat</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Supported File Types</h6>
        <p>You can upload <strong>any file type</strong> — documents, spreadsheets, PDFs, images, archives, etc. The following have special handling:</p>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Images</strong> (JPG, PNG, GIF, WebP)</td><td>Show an inline preview thumbnail in chat. Click to view full size.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Documents</strong> (PDF, DOC, XLS, etc.)</td><td>Show as a download link with file name and size.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Other files</strong></td><td>Show as a downloadable attachment with file name and size.</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>File Security</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Files are stored securely on the server — not accessible via direct URL</li>
          <li>Only participants of the conversation or task can download the file</li>
          <li>Chat files, task files, admin chat files, and bridge chat files are all stored in <strong>separate directories</strong></li>
          <li>When you <strong>delete a message</strong> that contains a file, the file is permanently removed from the server</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Downloading Files</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Click the <strong>file name</strong> or <strong>download icon</strong> to save the file to your computer</li>
          <li>For images, click the thumbnail to view full size, then right-click to save</li>
          <li>File downloads are authenticated — you must be logged in to download</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ ROLES & HIERARCHY (Admin only) ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-roles" style="display:none">
      <h4>Roles & Hierarchy</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">Understanding the power structure in the Client Portal.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Role Hierarchy (Top to Bottom)</h6>
        <div class="help-hierarchy">
          <div class="help-hierarchy-item level-1">
            <div class="help-hierarchy-badge admin">ADMIN</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Client Admin (Owner)</strong>
              <p>Full control. Can do everything — manage users, see all tasks, access Team India, assign to anyone.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="help-hierarchy-item level-2">
            <div class="help-hierarchy-badge top-mgmt">TOP MGMT</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Top Management (C-Suite)</strong>
              <p>Can access Team India, see all tasks, create tasks, assign to Top Mgmt and below. Cannot manage users.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="help-hierarchy-item level-3">
            <div class="help-hierarchy-badge mgmt">MGMT</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Management</strong>
              <p>Can create tasks, assign to Mgmt, Manager, and User level. Cannot see Team India or all tasks — only their own.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="help-hierarchy-item level-4">
            <div class="help-hierarchy-badge manager">MANAGER</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Manager</strong>
              <p>Can create tasks, assign to Managers and Users. Cannot assign upward. Sees only their own tasks.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="help-hierarchy-item level-5">
            <div class="help-hierarchy-badge user-role">USER</div>
            <div>
              <strong>User</strong>
              <p>Can view and update assigned tasks, participate in chats. Cannot create tasks or groups.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Assignment Rules</h6>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          <strong>Golden Rule:</strong> You can assign tasks to people at your level or below — never upward.
        </div>
        <table class="help-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Role</th><th>Can Assign To</th></tr></thead>
          <tr><td>Admin</td><td>Everyone (Admin, Top Mgmt, Mgmt, Manager, User)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Top Mgmt</td><td>Top Mgmt, Mgmt, Manager, User</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Mgmt</td><td>Mgmt, Manager, User</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Manager</td><td>Manager, User</td></tr>
          <tr><td>User</td><td>Cannot assign tasks</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Important Notes for Admin</h6>
        <div class="help-callout warning">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill me-2"></i>
          <ul style="margin:0;padding-left:1rem;">
            <li>Only you (Admin) can create, edit, deactivate, or reset passwords for portal users</li>
            <li>Role labels are hidden from all users — no one sees anyone else's role in the UI</li>
            <li>Team India is only visible to you and Top Management</li>
            <li>You cannot create another Admin — there is only one Admin account</li>
            <li>Deactivated users cannot log in but their data (messages, tasks, notes) is preserved</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ TEAM MANAGEMENT (Admin only) ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-team-mgmt" style="display:none">
      <h4>Team Management</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">Add, edit, and manage your portal team members.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Adding a New Member</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Go to the <strong>Team</strong> tab in the navigation</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Add Member</strong></li>
          <li>Fill in: <strong>Name</strong>, <strong>Email</strong>, <strong>Password</strong> (min 6 characters), and <strong>Role</strong></li>
          <li>Click <strong>Add Member</strong> to create the account</li>
          <li>Share the login credentials (email + password) with the new user securely</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          Available roles when creating a user: <strong>Top Management</strong>, <strong>Management</strong>, <strong>Manager</strong>, and <strong>User</strong>. You cannot create another Admin.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Managing Members</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-pencil me-2"></i><strong>Edit</strong></td><td>Change name, email, or role of an existing user</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-key me-2"></i><strong>Reset Password</strong></td><td>Set a new password for the user (min 6 characters)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-person-slash me-2"></i><strong>Deactivate</strong></td><td>Block the user from logging in — all their data is preserved</td></tr>
          <tr><td><i class="bi bi-person-check me-2"></i><strong>Activate</strong></td><td>Re-enable a deactivated user — they can log in again immediately</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Good to Know</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Changing a user's role takes effect immediately — no need for them to re-login</li>
          <li>Deactivated users appear greyed out in the team list</li>
          <li>You cannot delete a user — only deactivate. This preserves all their history.</li>
          <li>The email address must be unique — no two users can share the same email</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

