    <!-- ═══ SECURITY & SESSIONS ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-security" style="display:none">
      <h4>Security & Sessions</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">How the portal keeps your data safe and private.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Portal Privacy</h6>
        <div class="help-callout success">
          <i class="bi bi-shield-check me-2"></i>
          The Client Portal is <strong>completely invisible</strong> to the local team. They cannot see, access, or even know it exists. Your conversations, tasks, and notes are fully private.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Password Requirements</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Minimum length</strong></td><td>6 characters</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Special characters</strong></td><td>Not required, but recommended for stronger security</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Case sensitivity</strong></td><td>Passwords are case-sensitive (abc is different from ABC)</td></tr>
        </table>
        <div class="help-callout warning">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill me-2"></i>
          Choose a strong password. Avoid using common words, your name, or easily guessable information.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Login & Sessions</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Your login session is maintained via a secure authentication token</li>
          <li>The session persists until you <strong>log out</strong> or the token expires</li>
          <li>You can only be logged in on <strong>one browser tab</strong> at a time — opening the portal in a new tab shares the same session</li>
          <li>If your session expires, you'll be redirected to the login page automatically</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Logging Out</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Click your name in the <strong>top-right corner</strong></li>
          <li>Select <strong>Logout</strong></li>
          <li>You'll be taken back to the login page</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          Always log out when using a shared or public computer. Your session token is stored in the browser.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Data Separation</h6>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Portal chat</strong> data is stored in separate database tables from the local team's chat</li>
          <li><strong>Portal tasks</strong> are completely separate from the local team's tasks</li>
          <li><strong>Notes</strong> are private to each individual user — even the admin cannot read your notes</li>
          <li><strong>Files</strong> are stored in separate directories for portal, bridge, and task attachments</li>
          <li><strong>Bridge chat</strong> is the only point of contact between portal and local — and it's controlled by you</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ SETTINGS ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-settings" style="display:none">
      <h4>Settings & Password</h4>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Change Your Password</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Click your name in the top-right corner</li>
          <li>Select <strong>Change Password</strong></li>
          <li>Enter your new password (minimum 6 characters)</li>
          <li>Confirm the new password in the second field</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Update</strong></li>
        </ol>
        <div class="help-callout info">
          <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
          Your new password takes effect immediately. You do not need to log out and back in.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Switch Theme</h6>
        <p>Click the <strong>sun/moon icon</strong> (<i class="bi bi-sun"></i> / <i class="bi bi-moon"></i>) in the top-right to toggle between dark and light mode.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your preference is saved automatically in your browser</li>
          <li>The theme affects the entire portal — chat, tasks, notes, and all pages</li>
          <li>Dark mode is easier on the eyes for extended use, especially at night</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Forgot Your Password?</h6>
        <p>There is no self-service password reset. Contact your <strong>Admin</strong> and ask them to reset your password from the <strong>Team</strong> page.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ TIPS ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-tips" style="display:none">
      <h4>Tips & Shortcuts</h4>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Keyboard Shortcuts</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><kbd>Enter</kbd></td><td>Send message in chat</td></tr>
          <tr><td><kbd>Shift + Enter</kbd></td><td>New line in message (without sending)</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Chat Pro Tips</h6>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Scroll up</strong> in any chat to load older messages automatically — no button needed</li>
          <li><strong>Date separators</strong> — labels like "Today", "Yesterday", or "Apr 3, 2026" appear between message groups</li>
          <li><strong>URLs are clickable</strong> — paste any link and it becomes clickable automatically</li>
          <li><strong>Images preview inline</strong> — send an image and it shows as a thumbnail in the chat</li>
          <li><strong>Search within chat</strong> — click the search icon in the chat header to find specific messages</li>
          <li><strong>Edit typos fast</strong> — hover over your message, click three dots, edit and save</li>
          <li><strong>Emoji picker closes</strong> — click anywhere outside the emoji panel to dismiss it</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Task Pro Tips</h6>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Click a toast notification</strong> — task toasts take you directly to that task</li>
          <li><strong>Filter by status</strong> — quickly see only open or in-progress tasks</li>
          <li><strong>Check overdue tasks daily</strong> — tasks past their due date are highlighted in red</li>
          <li><strong>Edit comments</strong> — hover over your comment and click the pencil to fix mistakes</li>
          <li><strong>Dictate everything</strong> — the mic works in task title, description, and comments</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>Notes Pro Tips</h6>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Auto-save</strong> — just type, no need to press save. It saves 2 seconds after you stop</li>
          <li><strong>Pin important notes</strong> — pinned notes always stay at the top of your list</li>
          <li><strong>Export to PDF</strong> — click print icon, then use "Save as PDF" in your browser's print dialog</li>
          <li><strong>Dictate notes</strong> — click the mic button and speak instead of typing</li>
          <li><strong>Search notes</strong> — use the search bar to find notes by title or content</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6>General Pro Tips</h6>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Use Chrome or Edge</strong> — dictation and all features work best on these browsers</li>
          <li><strong>Dark mode at night</strong> — toggle the theme for comfortable viewing</li>
          <li><strong>Admin Chat from anywhere</strong> — the headset button is always in the top-right, on every page</li>
          <li><strong>Notification sounds</strong> — keep your volume up to never miss a message or task update</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ TROUBLESHOOTING ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-troubleshooting" style="display:none">
      <h4>Troubleshooting</h4>
      <p class="help-lead">Common issues and how to fix them.</p>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-mic-mute me-2"></i>Dictation Not Working</h6>
        <div class="help-callout danger">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-octagon-fill me-2"></i>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Clicking the mic button does nothing, or it immediately stops.
        </div>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Check browser</strong></td><td>Dictation only works in <strong>Chrome</strong> and <strong>Edge</strong>. Firefox and Safari do not fully support it.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Check microphone permission</strong></td><td>Click the lock/info icon in the browser address bar and make sure microphone is set to <strong>Allow</strong>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Check system microphone</strong></td><td>Ensure your microphone is connected and not muted in your computer's sound settings.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>HTTPS required</strong></td><td>Speech recognition requires a secure connection (HTTPS) or localhost. If on HTTP, it won't work.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Try refreshing</strong></td><td>Sometimes a simple page refresh fixes the issue.</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-chat-left-dots me-2"></i>Messages Not Appearing</h6>
        <div class="help-callout danger">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-octagon-fill me-2"></i>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> You sent a message but it doesn't show up, or you're not receiving messages.
        </div>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Check your connection</strong></td><td>Ensure you have a stable internet connection. The portal uses real-time WebSocket connections.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Refresh the page</strong></td><td>Press <kbd>F5</kbd> or <kbd>Ctrl+R</kbd> to reload. This re-establishes the connection.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Check if logged in</strong></td><td>If your session expired, you may need to log in again.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Clear browser cache</strong></td><td>Press <kbd>Ctrl+Shift+Delete</kbd>, clear cached files, and reload.</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-box-arrow-in-right me-2"></i>Can't Log In</h6>
        <div class="help-callout danger">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-octagon-fill me-2"></i>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Login fails with wrong credentials or an error message.
        </div>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Check email & password</strong></td><td>Passwords are case-sensitive. Make sure Caps Lock is off.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Account deactivated?</strong></td><td>Your admin may have deactivated your account. Contact them to check.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Forgot password?</strong></td><td>There is no self-service reset. Ask your admin to reset it from the Team page.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Browser issue</strong></td><td>Try a different browser or clear cookies for this site.</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-file-earmark-x me-2"></i>File Upload Failed</h6>
        <div class="help-callout danger">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-octagon-fill me-2"></i>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> File doesn't upload or you get an error.
        </div>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Check file size</strong></td><td>Maximum file size is <strong>100 MB</strong>. Larger files will be rejected.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Check connection</strong></td><td>Large files need a stable connection. If it drops mid-upload, the file won't be sent.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Try again</strong></td><td>Sometimes a retry works if the server was temporarily busy.</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-bell-slash me-2"></i>Not Receiving Notifications</h6>
        <div class="help-callout danger">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-octagon-fill me-2"></i>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Toast notifications or sounds are not appearing.
        </div>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Check browser tab</strong></td><td>Notifications work when the portal tab is open. If you close it, notifications stop.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Check system volume</strong></td><td>Notification sounds require your volume to be unmuted and turned up.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Active chat suppression</strong></td><td>If you're already viewing a conversation, you won't get a toast for it — the message just appears in the chat.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Refresh the page</strong></td><td>A page refresh re-establishes the real-time connection needed for notifications.</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-emoji-frown me-2"></i>Emoji Picker Not Closing</h6>
        <div class="help-callout danger">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-octagon-fill me-2"></i>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> The emoji panel stays open and won't dismiss.
        </div>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Click outside</strong></td><td>Click anywhere outside the emoji panel to close it.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Click emoji icon again</strong></td><td>Clicking the smiley face icon again will also close the panel.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Press Escape</strong></td><td>Some browsers support pressing Escape to close popups.</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="help-block">
        <h6><i class="bi bi-display me-2"></i>Page Looks Broken or Unstyled</h6>
        <table class="help-table">
          <tr><td><strong>Hard refresh</strong></td><td>Press <kbd>Ctrl+Shift+R</kbd> (or <kbd>Cmd+Shift+R</kbd> on Mac) to bypass browser cache.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Clear cache</strong></td><td>Clear your browser's cached files and reload the page.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Try another browser</strong></td><td>If the issue persists, try Chrome or Edge for best compatibility.</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
    <div class="help-section" id="section-faq" style="display:none">
      <h4>Frequently Asked Questions</h4>

      <div class="help-faq">

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Can other people see my private chats?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">No. Every 1-to-1 conversation is completely sealed. Only you and the other person can see it. Group chats are only visible to their participants. Not even the admin can read your private conversations.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Can the local team see this portal?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">No. The Client Portal is completely invisible to the local team. They have no access and no awareness of it. The only connection is through bridge chat (Team India) and admin chat, which are controlled from the portal side.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Can I delete a message I sent by mistake?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">Yes. Hover over your sent message, click the three-dot menu, and select Delete. The message will show "This message was deleted" for both parties. If it was a file or image, the file is also permanently deleted from the server. This works for text messages, file messages, and image messages.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Can I edit a message after sending it?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">Yes. Hover over your sent message, click the three-dot menu, and select Edit. Make your changes and save. The message will show "(edited)" next to the timestamp so others know it was modified. You can only edit your own messages.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>What is the maximum file size I can upload?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">The maximum file size is 100 MB per file. This applies everywhere — chat attachments, task comment files, admin chat, and bridge chat. There is no restriction on file types — you can send documents, images, spreadsheets, PDFs, archives, and more.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Where are files and attachments stored?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">All files are stored securely on the server in separate directories — portal chat files, task comment files, bridge chat files, and admin chat files are each isolated. Only authenticated participants of the conversation or task can access the files. Files cannot be accessed via a direct URL.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>What happens when I deactivate a user?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">They cannot log in anymore, but all their data — messages, tasks, notes, and files — is preserved. You can reactivate them anytime and everything will be exactly as they left it. Deactivation is reversible and does not delete anything.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Does dictation work on all browsers?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">Dictation (speech-to-text) works best in Google Chrome and Microsoft Edge. It uses the browser's built-in Web Speech API. Safari has limited support. Firefox does not support it. You also need to grant microphone permission when prompted by the browser.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Can I see who's online right now?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">Yes. In the chat sidebar, a green dot next to a person's name means they're currently online in the portal. The chat header also shows "Online" or "Offline" when you open a conversation.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>I forgot my password. How do I reset it?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">There is no self-service password reset. Contact your admin and ask them to reset your password from the Team management page. They'll set a new temporary password that you can change after logging in.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Can I use the portal on my phone?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">The portal is web-based and works on mobile browsers (Chrome on Android, Safari on iPhone). The layout adapts to smaller screens. However, for the best experience — especially with features like dictation and file uploads — we recommend using a desktop or laptop.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>What happens to my notes if my account is deactivated?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">All your notes are preserved. When your account is reactivated, all your notes will be there exactly as you left them. Notes are private — no one (not even the admin) can access your notes.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>What is the difference between Admin Chat and Bridge Chat?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">Admin Chat is a direct line to the local team's admin — available to everyone from any page via the headset button. Bridge Chat is for messaging individual local team employees, available only from the Team India page (Admin and Top Mgmt only). Both cross the portal-local boundary, but serve different purposes.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Can I see other people's roles in the portal?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">No. Role labels are hidden throughout the portal. You won't see anyone's role next to their name. This is by design — the hierarchy exists for permission management, but the experience feels equal for all users.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Why can't I create tasks or groups?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">If you don't see the "New Task" or "New Group" button, your account has the User role. Users can participate in chats and update assigned tasks, but cannot create new tasks or group chats. Contact your admin if you need elevated permissions.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Why can't I see Team India?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">The Team India page is only visible to Admin and Top Management roles. If you don't see it in the navigation, your role doesn't have access to this feature. Contact your admin if you need access.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="help-faq-item">
          <div class="help-faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
            <span>Do notification sounds play when the tab is in the background?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="help-faq-a">Notification sounds and toasts work when the portal tab is open (even in the background). However, if you close the tab entirely, notifications will not play. Keep the portal tab open to stay informed of new messages and task updates.</div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<script>
function showHelpSection(id) {
  document.querySelectorAll('.help-section').forEach(s => s.style.display = 'none');
  document.querySelectorAll('.help-nav-item').forEach(a => a.classList.remove('active'));
  const section = document.getElementById('section-' + id);
  if (section) section.style.display = '';
  event.target.classList.add('active');
}
</script>
